---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Sommeliers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Sommeliers working internationally, covering wine service positions abroad, hospitality careers, and global wine industry opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Sommeliers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Sommeliers working abroad, serving wine internationally, and pursuing careers across global hospitality and wine establishments.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/sommelier-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/sommelier-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Sommelier Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Sommeliers are wine experts who guide dining experiences—curating wine lists, recommending pairings, managing cellars, and educating guests about wine. International sommelier careers offer opportunities to explore world wine regions, work in premier dining establishments, and develop expertise across global wine cultures.
      </p>
      <p>
        International sommelier opportunities exist through Michelin restaurants, luxury hotels, cruise lines, wine importers, and private estates worldwide.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Sommeliers working abroad across global hospitality and wine establishments.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Sommeliers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Sensory protection', why: 'Taste and smell essential', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Service floor demands', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Wine region visits', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Service pressure', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Wellness support', why: 'Evening service schedule', typical: 'Often included' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Sensory Acuity</h3>
      <p>
        A sommelier's career depends on sensory perception—taste and smell are the essential tools of the profession. Loss of olfactory or gustatory function is career-ending. Illnesses affecting the senses, even temporarily, disrupt work. Protecting sensory health is uniquely critical for sommelier careers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Coverage that addresses sensory health protects the fundamental tools of sommelier work.
      </p>

      <h3>Service Environment</h3>
      <p>
        Sommeliers work the dining floor—standing for long service periods, navigating dining rooms, carrying and presenting bottles. The physical demands of fine dining service create ergonomic stress. Evening and weekend work is standard in the profession.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Michelin Restaurant</h3>
      <p>
        Fine dining establishment. Restaurant benefits vary. Excellence focus. Fine dining offers prestige.
      </p>

      <h3>Luxury Hotel</h3>
      <p>
        Five-star property. Hotel benefits. Multiple outlets possible. Hotels offer stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Cruise Line</h3>
      <p>
        Ship beverage program. Cruise line benefits. Guest education. Cruises offer travel.
      </p>

      <h3>Wine Import/Distribution</h3>
      <p>
        Wine trade. Company benefits. Business focus. Trade offers variety.
      </p>

      <h3>Private</h3>
      <p>
        Private estate or collection. Owner-provided benefits. Exclusive service. Private offers intimacy.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Sommeliers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Sommeliers working abroad across global hospitality and wine establishments."
      buttonText="Compare Sommelier Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Sommelier Certification</h3>
      <p>
        Court of Master Sommeliers. WSET. Other certifications. Certification validates knowledge.
      </p>

      <h3>Master Sommelier</h3>
      <p>
        Highest certification. Rare achievement. Industry recognition. MS represents excellence.
      </p>

      <h3>Wine Knowledge</h3>
      <p>
        Regional expertise. Vintage knowledge. Producer relationships. Knowledge enables service.
      </p>

      <h3>Service Skills</h3>
      <p>
        Guest interaction. Sales ability. Hospitality excellence. Service completes experience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Sensory Health</h3>
      <p>
        Taste preservation. Smell protection. Illness prevention. Sensory coverage critical.
      </p>

      <h3>Floor Work</h3>
      <p>
        Standing service. Dining room navigation. Bottle presentation. Ergonomic coverage valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Schedule</h3>
      <p>
        Evening service. Weekend work. Holiday demands. Wellness support helpful.
      </p>

      <h3>Alcohol Exposure</h3>
      <p>
        Professional tasting. Moderation essential. Health awareness. General health coverage important.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Curation</h3>
      <p>
        Wine list development. Selection decisions. Value assessment. Curation defines program.
      </p>

      <h3>Service</h3>
      <p>
        Guest interaction. Wine presentation. Pairing recommendations. Service delivers experience.
      </p>

      <h3>Education</h3>
      <p>
        Staff training. Guest education. Knowledge sharing. Education builds appreciation.
      </p>

      <h3>Business</h3>
      <p>
        Purchasing. Inventory. Cost management. Business ensures viability.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Growing Field</h3>
      <p>
        Wine interest expanding. Hospitality growth. Expert demand. Field growing.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Wine Director. Beverage Director. Wine Buyer. Educator. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        Wine knowledge universal. Certifications recognized globally. Experience transfers. Skills portable.
      </p>

      <h3>Field Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        Natural wine. Sustainability. New regions. Field evolving continuously.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a sommelier considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Hotels and restaurants provide benefits. Wine knowledge universal. Certifications recognized. Service skills essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Hotels typically yes. Fine dining varies. Cruise lines comprehensive. Verify benefits.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is sensory health coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Critical for sommeliers. Taste and smell essential. Loss career-affecting. Sensory coverage valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do sommelier credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Wine knowledge universal. CMS and WSET recognized globally. Experience valued. Credentials highly portable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What regions offer international opportunities?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Wine capitals active. Major cities growing. Cruise lines global. Multiple opportunities available.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Wine interest growing. Fine dining expanding. Expertise valued. Outlook positive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating restaurant or hotel benefits. Prioritize coverage that protects sensory health. Ensure ergonomic coverage for service floor demands. Consider travel coverage for wine region visits.
      </p>
      <p>
        Sommeliers elevate dining experiences worldwide. Your coverage should support sommelier careers—addressing sensory health and service demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across wine service globally.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Wine Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Sommeliers working abroad across global hospitality and wine establishments."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
